        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 11:27PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1126 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cotulla, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cotulla, Gardendale, Woodward, Zella, Fowlerton, Millett, Los
Angeles, Artesia Wells, and Chaparral Wildlife Management Area.

This includes Interstate 35 between mile markers 53 and 82.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
